{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-20T15:32:11.475Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Few-shot prompting"},{"type":"text","text":" is a technique where you "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"provide demonstrations in the prompt to steer the model to better performance"},{"type":"text","text":". You give the AI a \"mini training session inside your prompt\" by showing examples of how you want something done before it does the task."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The term \"shot\" equals an "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"example"},{"type":"text","text":". Few-shot = 2+ examples. One-shot = one example. Zero-shot = no examples."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"What Few-Shot Means"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Few-shot prompting can be used as a technique to enable in-context learning where we provide demonstrations in the prompt to steer the model to better performance."},{"type":"text","text":" The demonstrations serve as conditioning for subsequent examples where we'd like the model to generate a response."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Instruction: Classify emails into Billing, Bug, Feature, or Other.\n\nExamples:\nEmail: \"I was double charged this month and my receipt shows two payments.\"\n→ Category: Billing\nReason: The email is about incorrect charging.\n\nEmail: \"The app crashes every time I click 'Export to CSV'.\"\n→ Category: Bug\nReason: A specific feature is crashing.\n\nEmail: \"It would be great if the dashboard could export directly to Google Sheets.\"\n→ Category: Feature\nReason: User is requesting a new capability.\n\nNow label this email:\n\"Can you add a dark mode option to the settings page?\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here, the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"examples serve as demonstrations"},{"type":"text","text":" that teach the model the format and reasoning pattern before it processes the new input."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key Characteristics of Few-Shot"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":"left"},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Characteristic"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":"left"},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Few-Shot Value"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Examples"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"2+ demonstrations"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Complexity"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"More complex than zero-shot"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Token usage"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Higher (includes examples)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Cost"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Higher than zero-shot"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Accuracy"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Can significantly improve performance"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Control"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"High (you define the format and style)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best for"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Complex tasks, structured outputs, nuanced classification"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"How Few-Shot Works"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Few-shot prompting "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"enables in-context learning"},{"type":"text","text":". The model learns patterns from the examples you provide and applies them to the new input."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key finding from Min et al. (2022):"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"The "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"label space"},{"type":"text","text":" and the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"distribution of the input text"},{"type":"text","text":" specified by the demonstrations are both important\" (regardless of whether labels are correct for individual inputs)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"format you use plays a key role"},{"type":"text","text":" in performance—even random labels are better than no labels at all"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Selecting random labels from a true distribution"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of uniform distribution) also helps"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This means:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Show the model the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"range of possible outputs"},{"type":"text","text":" (label space)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"consistent format"},{"type":"text","text":" across examples"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Match the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"distribution"},{"type":"text","text":" of examples to what you expect in real use"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When to Use Few-Shot"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Primary Use Cases"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"1. Complex tasks where zero-shot fails"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"While large-language models demonstrate remarkable zero-shot capabilities, they still fall short on more complex tasks when using the zero-shot setting. Few-shot prompting can significantly improve performance on complex tasks."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When to use:"},{"type":"text","text":" When zero-shot results are poor or inconsistent."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"2. Structured outputs (like JSON)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Few-shot prompting is ideal for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"structured outputs (like JSON)"},{"type":"text","text":" or maintaining a specific tone. It offers more control and accuracy than zero-shot."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Task: Extract name, email, and phone from text.\n\nExamples:\nText: \"Hi, I'm John Smith. You can reach me at john@example.com or 555-1234.\"\nJSON: {\n  \"name\": \"John Smith\",\n  \"email\": \"john@example.com\",\n  \"phone\": \"555-1234\"\n}\n\nText: \"Contact Sarah Johnson at sarah.j@company.com. Her phone is 555-5678.\"\nJSON: {\n  \"name\": \"Sarah Johnson\",\n  \"email\": \"sarah.j@company.com\",\n  \"phone\": \"555-5678\"\n}\n\nNow extract from this text:\n\"Reach out to Mike Brown at mike.b@email.com. Phone: 555-9012\"\nJSON:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Format is critical here. Few-shot ensures the model follows it consistently."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"3. Nuanced classification"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Few-shot is ideal for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"nuanced classification"},{"type":"text","text":" tasks where the model needs to understand subtle distinctions."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Task: Classify emails into Billing, Bug, Feature, or Other.\n\nExamples:\nEmail: \"I was double charged.\"\n→ Category: Billing\nReason: The email is about incorrect charging.\n\nEmail: \"The app crashes when I click Export.\"\n→ Category: Bug\nReason: A specific feature is crashing.\n\nEmail: \"Export is too slow.\"\n→ Category: Bug (not Feature, because it's a performance issue)\n\nEmail: \"I'd love an Export feature.\"\n→ Category: Feature (because it's a new capability request)\n\nNow label this email:\n\"The app crashes when I click Export.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The edge cases (slow vs. feature) help the model understand the distinction."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"4. Writing consistency (voice & tone)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Few-shot is excellent for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"maintaining a specific tone"},{"type":"text","text":" or writing style across multiple outputs."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Task: Write a follow-up email after a sales call.\n\nExamples:\nInput: \"Met with Sarah from TechCorp. She's interested in our analytics feature but worried about pricing.\"\nOutput: \"Hi Sarah, Thank you for taking the time to speak with me yesterday. I enjoyed learning about TechCorp's goals and discussing how our analytics feature could help you track customer behavior more effectively. I understand pricing is a concern, and I'd be happy to explore options that fit your budget. Would you like to schedule a follow-up call to discuss next steps?\"\n\nInput: \"Spoke with John from DesignCo. He needs a quick solution for client reporting.\"\nOutput: \"Hi John, Thank you for the great conversation today! I'm excited about the possibility of helping DesignCo streamline your client reporting process. Our analytics platform can generate reports in under 5 minutes, which sounds like exactly what you need. Let's set up a time this week to get you started. When would work best for you?\"\n\nNow write an email for this input:\n\"Talked with Lisa from RetailPlus. She wants to automate her inventory tracking.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The examples show the tone (friendly, professional, solution-focused) the model should match."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Few-Shot vs. Zero-Shot: Comparison"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":"left"},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Aspect"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":"left"},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Zero-Shot"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":"left"},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Few-Shot"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Examples"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"None"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"2+ demonstrations"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Token usage"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Low"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Higher (includes examples)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Cost"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Low"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Higher"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Accuracy"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Baseline"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Can significantly improve"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Control"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Low (model decides format)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"High (you define format)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best for"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Simple tasks, baseline testing"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Complex tasks, structured outputs"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Flexibility"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"High (works for many tasks)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Lower (examples constrain scope)"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best Practices for Few-Shot Prompting"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"1. Use 3–5 Well-Chosen Examples"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Anthropic recommends using "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"3–5 realistic examples"},{"type":"text","text":" that show edge cases and ideal style. More than 5 may consume too much context."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why?"},{"type":"text","text":" Too many examples waste tokens; too few may not teach the pattern well."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"2. Show Edge Cases and Variety"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Include examples that cover:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Common cases"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Edge cases (ambiguous situations)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Negative cases (looks like X but is actually Y)"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Email: \"The app crashes when I click Export.\"\n→ Category: Bug\n\nEmail: \"Export is too slow.\"\n→ Category: Bug (not Feature, because it's a performance issue)\n\nEmail: \"I'd love an Export feature.\"\n→ Category: Feature (because it's a new capability request)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"3. Use Consistent Format"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"format you use plays a key role"},{"type":"text","text":" in performance—even random labels are better than no labels at all. Keep the format identical across all examples."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"BAD:\nEmail: \"I was double charged.\"\n→ Category: Billing\n\nEmail: \"The app crashes.\"\nCategory: Bug\nReason: The app is crashing.\n\nGOOD:\nEmail: \"I was double charged.\"\n→ Category: Billing\nReason: The email is about incorrect charging.\n\nEmail: \"The app crashes.\"\n→ Category: Bug\nReason: A specific feature is crashing."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"4. Select Examples from True Distribution"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Selecting random labels from a true distribution"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of uniform distribution) helps. Match the distribution of examples to what you expect in real use."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"},{"type":"hardBreak"},{"type":"text","text":"If 70% of your emails are \"Billing\" and 30% are \"Bug\", your examples should reflect that distribution."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"5. Use Tags to Separate Examples"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use XML-style tags like "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<examples>"},{"type":"text","text":" to clearly separate examples from instructions. This is especially effective with Claude, which responds well to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"XML structuring"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<examples>\nEmail: \"I was double charged.\"\n→ Category: Billing\nReason: The email is about incorrect charging.\n\nEmail: \"The app crashes.\"\n→ Category: Bug\nReason: A specific feature is crashing.\n</examples>"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"6. Use the Optimal Number of Examples"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Research suggests there's an "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"optimal number of examples"},{"type":"text","text":" (usually 3–5). Too few may not teach the pattern; too many waste tokens and may confuse the model."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"7. Test with Different Example Sequences"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"sequence of examples can impact results"},{"type":"text","text":". Try different orders and see which works best."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Real-World Examples"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example 1: Sentiment Classification (3-shot)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Instruction: Classify the text into neutral, negative, or positive.\n\nExamples:\nInput: \"I love this product!\"\nOutput: Positive\n\nInput: \"This is terrible.\"\nOutput: Negative\n\nInput: \"It's okay.\"\nOutput: Neutral\n\nNow classify this:\nInput: \"I think the food was okay.\"\nOutput:"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example 2: Code Explanation (2-shot)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Task: Explain what each function does in plain English.\n\nExamples:\n```python\ndef add(a, b):\n    return a + b\n```\nExplanation: This function takes two numbers and returns their sum.\n\n```python\ndef greet(name):\n    print(f\"Hello, {name}!\")\n```\nExplanation: This function takes a name and prints a greeting message.\n\nNow explain this:\n```python\ndef calculate_total(items):\n    total = 0\n    for item in items:\n        total += item.price\n    return total\n```\nExplanation:"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example 3: Sales Call → Follow-up Email (3-shot)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Task: Write a follow-up email after a sales call.\n\nExamples:\nInput: \"Met with Sarah from TechCorp. She's interested in analytics but worried about pricing.\"\nOutput: \"Hi Sarah, Thank you for taking the time to speak with me yesterday. I enjoyed learning about TechCorp's goals...\"\n\nInput: \"Spoke with John from DesignCo. He needs a quick solution for client reporting.\"\nOutput: \"Hi John, Thank you for the great conversation today! I'm excited about helping DesignCo streamline your client reporting...\"\n\nInput: \"Talked with Lisa from RetailPlus. She wants to automate inventory tracking.\"\nOutput:"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Common Mistakes with Few-Shot"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Mistake 1: Inconsistent Format"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Bad:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Email: \"I was double charged.\"\n→ Category: Billing\n\nEmail: \"The app crashes.\"\nCategory: Bug\nReason: The app is crashing."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ Good:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Email: \"I was double charged.\"\n→ Category: Billing\nReason: The email is about incorrect charging.\n\nEmail: \"The app crashes.\"\n→ Category: Bug\nReason: A specific feature is crashing."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Mistake 2: Too Many Examples"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Bad:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example 1: \"I was double charged.\" → Billing\nExample 2: \"The app crashes.\" → Bug\nExample 3: \"Export is slow.\" → Bug\nExample 4: \"I'd love Export.\" → Feature\nExample 5: \"Payment failed.\" → Billing\nExample 6: \"Login broken.\" → Bug\n... (10 more examples)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ Good:"},{"type":"text","text":" 3–5 well-chosen examples."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Mistake 3: Not Showing Edge Cases"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Bad:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Email: \"I was double charged.\" → Billing\nEmail: \"The app crashes.\" → Bug\nEmail: \"I want dark mode.\" → Feature"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ Good:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Email: \"The app crashes when I click Export.\" → Bug\nEmail: \"Export is too slow.\" → Bug (not Feature, it's a performance issue)\nEmail: \"I'd love an Export feature.\" → Feature (it's a new capability)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Summary"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Few-shot prompting"},{"type":"text","text":" is a technique that provides "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"demonstrations in the prompt to enable in-context learning"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Definition"},{"type":"text","text":": 2+ examples shown before the task"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When to use"},{"type":"text","text":": Complex tasks, structured outputs (JSON), nuanced classification, maintaining tone"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"How it works"},{"type":"text","text":": Examples serve as conditioning for the model to learn patterns"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits"},{"type":"text","text":": Significantly improves accuracy, high control over format, better for complex tasks"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Trade-offs"},{"type":"text","text":": Higher token usage, higher cost, less flexible than zero-shot"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key principles:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use 3–5 examples"},{"type":"text","text":" (optimal number)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Show edge cases and variety"},{"type":"text","text":" (ambiguity, negative cases)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use consistent format"},{"type":"text","text":" (format matters more than label accuracy)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Match true distribution"},{"type":"text","text":" (not uniform distribution)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use XML tags"},{"type":"text","text":" to separate examples"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Test different sequences"},{"type":"text","text":" (order impacts results)"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Strategy:"},{"type":"text","text":" Start with "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Zero-Shot"},{"type":"text","text":" initially, switch to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Few-Shot"},{"type":"text","text":" if more accuracy or specific formatting is required, and escalate to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Chain-of-Thought"},{"type":"text","text":" when tasks involve multi-step reasoning."}]}]}}
